Legendary jazz musician Hugh Masekela has died. A family member confirmed to HuffPost that the 78-year-old succumbed to cancer on Tuesday. In a career spanning more than five decades, Masekela gained international recognition with his distinctive Afro-Jazz sound and hits such as "Soweto Blues", which served as one of the soundtracks to the anti-apartheid movement, reports Reuters. Take a look at his life in pictures:  Share this slide: 